2025-04-28 11:35 ET - News Release
An anonymous director reports
DIVIDEND - CURRENCY ELECTION AND PAYMENT CURRENCY UPDATE
Thor Explorations Ltd. has provided an update to the dividend timetable announced on  April 8, 2024. The currency election date will now be  May 14, 2025. All other dates remain as previously announced. In addition, the company will pay the dividend in Canadian dollars, British pounds or U.S. dollars.
Maiden dividend payment timetable:
May 1, 2025 -- ex dividend date;
May 2, 2025 -- record date;
May 14, 2025 -- last day of currency election;
May 15, 2025 -- announcement of exchange rate in foreign-designated currencies;
May 16, 2025 -- payment date.
About Thor Explorations Ltd.
Thor Explorations is a mineral exploration company engaged in the acquisition, exploration, development and production of mineral properties located in Nigeria, Senegal and Burkina Faso. Thor Explorations holds a 100-per-cent interest in the Segilola gold project located in Osun state, Nigeria, and has a 70-per-cent economic interest in the Douta gold project located in southeastern Senegal. Thor Explorations trades on AIM (Alternative Investment Market) and the TSX Venture Exchange under the symbol THX.
